Create a navigation bar using HTML and CSS.

Use HTML to create a navigation bar with appropriate tags such as <ul> and <li>.

Use CSS to style the navigation bar with appropriate properties such as background-color, font-size, and padding

nav.html

<nav>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="#">Home</a></li>
    <li><a href="#">About</a></li>
    <li><a href="#">Services</a></li>
    <li><a href="#">Contact</a></li>
  </ul>
</nav>

nav.css

nav {
  background-color: #333;
  height: 50px;
  padding: 10px;
}

nav ul {
  list-style: none;
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
}

nav li {
  float: left;
}

nav a {
  display: block;
  color: #fff;
  font-size: 18px;
  line-height: 50px;
  padding: 0 20px;
  text-decoration: none;
}

nav a:hover {
  background-color: #555;
}
